                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits of Texts I-II and their
                           sections; names of the donors; directives to the ministers; abbreviations
                           of the directives yǝbǝl kahǝn, “the priest says”, yǝbǝl diyaqon, “the
                           deacon says”, yǝbǝl ḥǝzb, “the people say”, yǝbǝl kahǝn nǝfq, “the
                           assistant priest says”; titles of books to be read; names of the weekdays
                           indicating daily readings of Text II; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 On the incipit pages of Text I (fols.
                           3r, 4v) a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
